  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Ramji Prasad Jaiswal @ Ramjee Prasad Jaiswal and Ors. versus State of Bihar pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_6_582_600','2025INSC738'); ><font size='4'> <strong>RAMJI PRASAD JAISWAL @ RAMJEE PRASAD JAISWAL AND ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF BIHAR </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 582</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 738</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002122025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the facts of the case there was a breach of s.313, CrPC causing prejudice to the appellants and vitiating the trial against them. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.313 &ndash; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.420, 468, 471, 120B &ndash; &ndash; ss.5(2), 5(1)(d) &ndash; Appellants were convicted u/ss.420, 468, 471, 120B, IPC r/w ss.5(2), 5(1)(d), PC Act and sentenced accordingly &ndash; Incriminating circumstances which had come on record against them in the prosecution evidence were not put to them in their examination u/s.313<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 19-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 490/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_6_582_600','2025INSC738','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns m